com.opengamma.strata.engine.marketdata.mapping

Interface MarketDataMappings

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultMarketDataMappings

    public interface MarketDataMappings
    Market data mappings specify which market data from the global set of data should be used for a particular calculation.

    For example, the global set of market data might contain curves from several curve groups but a calculation needs to request (for example) the USD discounting curve without knowing or caring which group contains it.

    This class provides the mapping from a general piece of data (the USD discounting curve) to a specific piece of data (the USD discounting curve from the curve group named 'XYZ').

      • getIdForKey

        <T,K extends MarketDataKey<T>> MarketDataId<T> getIdForKey(K key)
        Returns a market data ID which uniquely identifies the piece of market data referred to by the key.

        The key might identify an item of data of which there are many copies in the system, for example the USD discounting curve. The ID identifies a globally unique copy, for example the USD discounting curve from a named curve group.

        Type Parameters:
        K - the type of the market data key accepted by this method
        T - the type of the data returned by the key
        Parameters:
        key - a key identifying an item of market data
        Returns:
        an ID uniquely identifying an item of market data

      • getIdForObservableKey

        Gets the market data ID for an item of observable market data given its key.
        Parameters:
        key - a market data key identifying an item of observable market data
        Returns:
        a market data ID that uniquely identifies the data and its source
